obo:BFO_0000066  a  owl:ObjectProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_720  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Subcellular fractionation and Western Blot with an isoform-specific antibody against gamma-SNAP (SNAP= soluble N-ethylmaleimide fusion protein attachment protein) indicates that gamma-SNAP is present in membrane and soluble fractions of synaptosomes (Fig.3).\n\nIsoform-specific anti-SNAP antibodies were raised to the sequence: (C)EGTAAPAAEEEEDEYAGGL (anti-γ-SNAP, residues 309-327 of γ-SNAP). Immunoblotting analysis demonstrates the specificity of the antibody (Fig.1). Experimental description: Subcellular fractions of rat brain homogenate were prepared according to procedures originally described by...\n\nUniprot accession A0A0G2K350 was retrieved via multi-step blast strategy against the peptide epitope used in the publication to raise the antibody." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" ;
        dc:date           "2017-06-06" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_720" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

